UNIDENTIFIED DISEASE Â– GHANA (WASSA AMENFI)
*******************************************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Sun 10 Oct 1999
From: ProMED promed@usa.healthnet.org
Source: Africa News Online Wed 6 Oct 1999 [edited]
http://www.africanews.org/health

An outbreak of unidentified disease has been reported in Breman, in the
district of Wassa Amenfi, in Ghana.
145 cases were notified, including 4 deaths. The symptoms were described as
being dizzyness, vomiting & convulsions. The local authorities suspect
poisoning, possibly by organophosphates.
